Shinner also took the image used on the family's Christmas card this year.

In their Christmas card image, released earlier this month, the family was seen together in another black and white photo arranged around Princess Charlotte sitting on a chair.

In the picture the couple shared on Christmas Day, the three children seem to be wearing the same clothes and shoes as in the Christmas card image.

This recent holiday portrait showcases the three siblings wearing matching outfits and shoes, reminiscent of their earlier festive photo released this month. The royal family is currently spending Christmas Day at Sandringham in Norfolk, where they will attend a morning church service. Before Christmas, the Princess of Wales hosted a carol service, Together At Christmas, at Westminster Abbey, which was televised on Christmas Eve.
